          "content:encoded":
            '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As the marketing head for our harmonica orchestra concert, I created the design below to represent the relationship between music and mathematical patterns.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Original design</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":664,"width":728,"height":582,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sciffany.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/screenshot-2020-02-01-at-3.28.15-pm.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-664" width="728" height="582" /></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Social media caption: "Whether you\'re a music lover 🎧🎶 or math nerd, you\'ll love NUS Harmonica Orchestra\'s Tessellations concert! Join us as we explore patterns and symmetry in music. Through lively pieces such as Libertango💃🏻, and whimsical pieces such as Waltz of the Flowers 🌺🌹, we present to you a concert which will make you move to the rhythm, dance to the melody, and and get you thinking about music 🎵✖🎶. Be there or be square!"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
